"A Radio Frequency Identification (RFID) yoking proof allows an off-line verifier to make sure whether two tags are simultaneously present. Due to offline property, a reader cannot differentiate valid from invalid proof records when it probes tags, and would generate lots of useless data. This paper proposes a treebased matched RFID yoking scheme which enhances the cost of identification from O(log N) to O(1), where N is the number of tags, and allows the reader to collect only those matched tags such that it significantly reduces useless data for the verifier to validate off-line."
